  "prompt": "How can I store 1TB of data online for free?",
  "response": "Storing 1TB of data online for free can be quite challenging as most cloud storage providers offer much smaller capacities for free. However, you can often combine multiple services or use promotional offers to achieve this. Here are a few strategies you might consider:\n\n1. **Google Drive**: Google offers 15GB of free storage per account. You could use multiple Google accounts to store more data.\n\n2. **Dropbox**: Dropbox gives 2GB for free initially, but you can earn additional space through referrals and other incentives. This won\u2019t get you close to 1TB, but it can help incrementally.\n\n3. **OneDrive**: Microsoft\u2019s OneDrive provides 5GB for free, and you can expand this with multiple accounts and promotional offers.\n\n4. **Mega**: Mega.nz offers 20GB of free storage, plus additional bonuses that vary over time.\n\n5. **Box**: Box provides 10GB of free storage for personal accounts.\n\n6. **PCloud**: PCloud offers 10GB of free storage.\n\n7. **HubiC**: HubiC offers 25GB for free.\n\nCombining accounts across these services might help you get closer to the 1TB goal. However, it can be cumbersome to manage multiple accounts and keep track of your data across different platforms.\n\n### Alternative Methods:\n- **University or Educational Discounts**: If you are a student or staff at a university, you might have access to heavily discounted or free cloud storage through your institution.\n  \n- **Promotional Offers**: Some companies offer temporary discounts or increased storage capacities for new users. Keeping an eye out for such promotions might be beneficial.\n\n- **Using External Hard Drives**: While not online storage, using external hard drives to store your data is a reliable alternative. If you need to transfer large files regularly, physical storage can complement online solutions.\n\nMake sure to read the terms and conditions of each service to ensure they fit your needs and that you are compliant with their acceptable use policies.",
